docs.abstract: For working-class voters in Dayton, Ohio, the Republican tax cuts are providing modest benefits, one paycheck at a time, but it is hardly life-changing.
docs.snippet: For working-class voters in Dayton, Ohio, the Republican tax cuts are providing modest benefits, one paycheck at a time, but it is hardly life-changing.
docs.lead_paragraph: DAYTON, Ohio — At Slyder’s Tavern, Matt Kazee, a machinist, drank a couple of beers as he waited for burgers to take home for dinner. His tab was about equal to the increase in his take-home pay after President Trump’s tax cut found its way into the nation’s paychecks.

headline.main: Blue-Collar Trump Voters Are Shrugging at Their Tax Cuts
headline.print_headline: Shrugging at a Tax Cut That Might Buy a Fill-Up
